I '''Steven Paul''' "'''Steve'''" '''Jobs''' (February 24, 1955&nbsp;- October 5, 2011)<ref name="NYT-20111005">{{cite news|last=Markoff |first=John |title=Steve Jobs, Apple's Visionary, Dies at 56|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/10/06/business/steve-jobs-of-apple-dies-at-56.html|work=[[The New York Times]] |date=October 5, 2011 |accessdate=October 5, 2011}}</ref><ref name="CNN">{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2011/10/05/us/obit-steve-jobs/index.html?iref=BN1&hpt=hp_t1 |title=Steve Jobs, Apple founder, dies |publisher=CNN |date=October 5, 2011 |accessdate=October 5, 2011}}</ref><ref name="AppleStatement">{{cite press release|url=http://www.apple.com/pr/library/2011/10/05Statement-by-Apples-Board-of-Directors.html|title=Statement by Apple's Board of Directors|publisher=Apple Inc.|date=October 5, 2011|accessdate=October 5, 2011}}</ref> metung yang imbentor ampong negosianting Americanu. Metung ya kareng talatátag ning [[Apple Inc.]], nung nu ya murin meging talapamuntuk (chairman) ampong pekapun a papalyaring manungkulan (chief executive officer).</ref> chairman, and chief executive officer of [[Apple Inc.]]<ref name="apple-2011pr-jobs-resigns">{{cite press release | url = http://www.apple.com/pr/library/2011/08/24Steve-Jobs-Resigns-as-CEO-of-Apple.html | title = Steve Jobs Resigns as CEO of Apple | publisher=Apple Inc. | date = August 24, 2011 | accessdate =August 24, 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Steve Jobs Resigns as Apple CEO |url=http://blogs.wsj.com/deals/2011/08/24/steve-jobs-resigns-as-apple-ceo/|accessdate=August 24, 2011 | work=The Wall Street Journal|first=Shira|last=Ovide|date=August 24, 2011}}</ref> Bayu ita, migsilbi ya mu namang pekapun a talapalyari ning [[Pixar|Pixar Animation Studios]]; megi yang kayanib ning lupung da reng manibala (board of directors) ning [[The Walt Disney Company]] anyang 2006, kaybat neng asali ning Disney ing Pixar. Kikilalanan deng executive producer ning ''[[Toy Story]]'' (1995).<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0114709/fullcredits IMDB, "Toy Story" Credits]</ref>

Anyang tawli nang dake ning dekadang 1970, i Jobs - kayabe da reng talatátag ning Apple, di [[Steve Wozniak]], [[Mike Markkula]]<ref name="Markkula1997"/> at aliwa pa - diniseniu de, inalkus, at pisali de ing metung kareng mumunang personal computer a misaling mayap king merkadu, ing [[Apple II series]]. Anyang umpisa ning dekadang 1980, metung ya i Jobs kareng mumunang menakit king malyaring maging sikanan na king merkadu ning [[PARC (kupanya)#The GUI|Xerox PARC's]] [[computer mouse|mouse]]-driven [[graphical user interface]], which led to the creation of the [[Macintosh]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.wired.com/gadgets/mac/news/2004/01/61730|title=Wired News: We're All Mac Users Now|work=Wired News|accessdate=September 20, 2006|last=Kahney|first=Leander|date=January 6, 2004}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://money.cnn.com/magazines/fortune/storysupplement/stevejobs/index.html|title=America's Most Admired Companies: Jobs' journey timeline|work=[[CNNMoney.com]] | accessdate=May 24, 2010}} Jobs and a team of engineers visit Xerox PARC, where they see a demo of mouse and graphical user interface</ref> Kaybat nang mesambut king metung a pamakilaban king upaya (power struggle) king lupung da reng manibala anyang 1985,<ref name="DNA200905">{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/money/report_what-steve-jobs-did-when-he-was-fired-from-apple_1254757|title=What Steve Jobs did when he was fired from Apple|work=[[DNA (newspaper)]]|author=Vivek Kaul|date=May 11, 2009}}</ref><ref name="commencement" /> meko ya king Apple i Jobs at tetag ne ing [[NeXT]], metung a kumpanyang manalkus [[computer platform]] development company (computer platform development company) a lalawang makabukud (specializing) kareng merkadung matas a pamagaral  (higher-education) ampong negosiu. Anyang seli ne ning Apple ing NeXT anyang 1996, mibalik ya i  Jobs king kumpanyang tetag na, at migsilbi ya antimong CEO (pekapun a talapalyaring manungkulan) manibat 1997 anggang 2011.

Anyang 1986, ikwa ne ing computer graphics division ning [[Lucasfilm|Lucasfilm Ltd]], a meging [[Pixar|Pixar Animation Studios]].<ref name="Pixar History 1986">{{cite web|url=http://www.pixar.com/companyinfo/history/1986.html|title=Pixar History&nbsp;- 1986|publisher=[[Pixar]]|accessdate=April 25, 2008}}</ref> Menatili/mindatila yang  CEO ampong manimunang shareholder king edad a 50.1&nbsp;percent anggang ikwa ne ning [[The Walt Disney Company]] anyang 2006.<ref name="Apple 2006">{{cite web|url=http://www.apple.com/pr/bios/jobs.html|title=Apple&nbsp;- Press Info&nbsp;- Bios&nbsp;- Steve Jobs|publisher=[[Apple Inc.]]|accessdate=September 20, 2006|year=2006|month=May}}</ref> Kaybat, i Jobs ing meging pekamaragul a indibidwal a shareholder ningDisney's largest individual a 7&nbsp;percent ampong kayanib ning Lupung da reng Talapanibala (Board of Directors) ning Disney.<ref name="DisneyBuysPixar" /><ref name="Disney">{{cite web|url=http://corporate.disney.go.com/corporate/bios/steve_jobs.html|title=The Walt Disney Company&nbsp;- Steve Jobs Biography}}<br /> {{cite news|accessdate=January 17, 2010|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/01/25/business/25disney.html|title=Disney Agrees to Acquire Pixar in a $7.4&nbsp;Billion Deal |work=The New York Times | first=Laura M. | last=Holson | date=January 25, 2006}}<br /> {{cite news|accessdate=January 17, 2010|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/05/06/business/media/06pixar.html|title=Pixar Becomes Unit of Disney|work=The New York Times | agency = Associated Press | date=May 6, 2006}}</ref> Anyang Agosto 24, 2011, pepabalu pepabalu nang Jobs ing kayang pamagdimiti o pamagkalag (resignation) antimong CEO ning Apple . 

Mete ya i Jobs king California anyang Octubre 5, 2011, king edad a 56 .<ref name="apple remembering">{{cite web|url=http://www.apple.com/stevejobs/|title=Remembering Steve Jobs|date=October 5, 2011|publisher=Apple Inc.|location=Cupertino, California|accessdate=October 5, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/ktla-apple-steve-jobs-dies,0,7477308.story|title=Steve Jobs: Apple Announces Former CEO Steve Jobs Has Died|work=Chicago Tribune|date=October 5, 2011|accessdate=October 5, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/2011/oct/06/steve-jobs-apple-cofounder-dies|publisher=[[The Guardian|www.guardian.co.uk]] |title=Steve Jobs, Apple co-founder, dies at 56|date=6 October 2011|first=Dominic |last=Rushe}}</ref>

